    "body": "I'm not sure which behaviour is better, but two more points: \n- I would say that \"no attack cursor\" (so that you have to force fire) makes sense if the spy is disguised as ally's unit, but not when disguised as the unit of a player who tries to select/target them. Your own units should \"identify/comply or die\" :) \n- Spies now also detect spies, no?\n"
